~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>At The Hero Heart Tavern</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
&quot;The tavern is busy tonight, very busy,&quot; thinks the bard to himself. &quot;Wouldn't hurt to sing this one, since they be busy a'chattin'. Doubt anyone will pay attention anyway.&quot; With that he begins to strum his harp:<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Seven days past the longest night<br>
Beneath a full moon's chilly light<br>
A secret labor lasts till dawn<br>
A child is born of elven spawn<br>
Lillies open to the sun<br>
<br>
A midwife's gasp, a mother's cringe,<br>
&quot;Tis as I fear, she's bluish tinged.<br>
Among Feir'dal she cannot live.<br>
Take the child, she must be hid.&quot;<br>
Lillies bask unto the warmth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take her to the caves of black,<br>
Her father's home in Neriak.<br>
Tell no one of her wood-elf dame<br>
Let they be those who give her name.&quot;<br>
Lillies dance unto the breeze.<br>
<br>
Within the day the midwife goes<br>
And hands the child to Eizabeau <br>
Exchanged beneath a willow tree<br>
Where she will grow on, strong and free.<br>
Dancing Lily beneath the Willows&quot;<br>
<br>
As the bard finishes his song, a woman brings a fresh pint to him with a quirky smile. &quot;Song doesn't specify that Eizabeau isn't in Neriak and that the midwife snuck the child out of the tower-of-crazies right back to the old Willowswood estate.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nope, it doesn't, does it. But then, no one really needs to know that the girl's skin faded to a nice wood-elf hue, well, 'cept when the tips of her ears get cold and go blue.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, still, the girl's been let out of the Training halls and running free in the hunting yard now with sword and bow. Don't be causing her any trouble letting skeletons out of closets. We don't even know if she knows of her parentage or not,&quot; she admonishes the bard.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes ma'am,&quot; the bard answers as he pretends to pout, and then moves on to another song.<br>
